Kaveel Singh, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Four drivers were arrested for speeding on the N3 southbound near Rand Airport on Sunday, Ekurhuleni metro police said.The fastest of the drivers was caught going 180km/h in a 120km/h zone at 06:40 on Sunday morning, spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Wilfred Kgasago said in a statement.The 33-year-old man had three male passengers in his red VW Golf 6 and claimed to be in a hurry to get home.He was locked up at the Germiston police station and charged with reckless or negligent driving.Three other drivers were caught going at 163, 165, and 166km/h and charged with the same offence. All were released on R1 000 bail each.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.